        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 25 at 5:01PM EDT by NWS Charleston WV</headline>
        <description>At 501 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking strong thunderstorms along
a line extending from near Buckhannon to 10 miles east of Glenville.
Movement was south at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Weston, Stonewall Jackson, Rock Cave, Burnsville, Flatwoods, Lorentz,
Stouts Mills, Sand Run, Alton, Heaters, Walkersville, Kanawha Head,
Ireland, Horner, French Creek, and Falls Mills.

This includes the following highways...
Interstate 79 near mile marker 68, and between mile markers 71 and
101.
Route 33 between mile markers 1 and 7.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
